<bibRefCitation author="Hansen, PEH" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Marine Sciences" pageId="9" pageNumber="66" pagination="313 - 354" title="Revision of the tripterygiid fish genus Helcogramma, including descriptions of four new species." volume="38" year="1986">Hansen (1986)</bibRefCitation>
. However, it had been recognised as a valid species and a senior synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Tripterygiidae" genus="Helcogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Helcogramma habena" order="Perciformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="habena">Helcogramma habena</taxonomicName>
(Williams &amp; McCormick, 1990) by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fricke, R" journalOrPublisher="Theses Zoologicae" pageId="9" pageNumber="66" pagination="1 - 607" title="Tripterygiid fishes of the western and central Pacific, with descriptions of 15 new species, including an annotated checklist of world Tripterygiidae (Teleostei)." volume="29" year="1997">Fricke (1997)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Williams, JT" journalOrPublisher="Aqua, Journal of Ichthyology and Aquatic Biology" pageId="9" pageNumber="66" pagination="151 - 176" title="Seven species of the triplefin fish genus Helcogramma (Tripterygiidae) from the Indo-Pacific." volume="7" year="2003">Williams and Howe (2003)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
